<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1985-10-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Sugar intolerance complicating acute gastroenteritis.</TITLE><BODY>Sugar intolerance occurred in 31 of 200 children admitted to hospital with acute gastroenteritis. In 28 this was transient and settled rapidly, but in the remaining three it indicated a more serious and persistent problem. The most important predisposing factor was viral infection, in particular with rotavirus. The current regimen for the management of sugar intolerance complicating acute gastroenteritis at this hospital is outlined.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>